  "text": "Vertical equity in healthcare financing is measured by analyzing the progressivity most commonly using the Kakwani Index of progressivity [CITATION_1] . The Kakwani index is defined as twice the area between a payment concentration curve for a payment (for taxes or health care etc.) and the Lorenz curve for income (or other measure of ability to pay). The index's value lies between −2 and 1. A negative index suggests regressivity (a lower proportion of income is paid out towards the payment as income increases) and a positive index suggests progressivity (a higher proportion of income is paid out towards the payment as income increases). The index, k, is calculated as",
